{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idb529a77a-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s280b–1b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"280b–1b"},"text":"§ 280b–1b.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Use of allotments for rape prevention education","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb529a77b-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s280b–1b/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Permitted use","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary, acting through the National Center for Injury Prevention and Control at the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, shall award targeted grants to States to be used for rape prevention and education programs conducted by rape crisis centers, State, territorial or tribal sexual assault coalitions, and other public and private nonprofit entities for—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb529a77c-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s280b–1b/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" educational seminars;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb529a77d-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s280b–1b/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the operation of hotlines or utilization of other communication technologies for purposes related to such a hotline;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb529a77e-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s280b–1b/a/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" training programs for professionals, including school-based professionals, to identify and refer students who may have experienced or are at risk of experiencing sexual violence;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb529a77f-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s280b–1b/a/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the preparation of informational material;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb529a780-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s280b–1b/a/5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" education and training programs for students and campus personnel designed to reduce the incidence of sexual assault at colleges and universities;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb529a781-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s280b–1b/a/6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"6"},"text":"(6)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" education to increase awareness about drugs and alcohol used to facilitate rapes or sexual assaults; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb529a782-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s280b–1b/a/7"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"7"},"text":"(7)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" other efforts to increase awareness of the facts about, or to help prevent, sexual violence, sexual assault, and sexual harassment, including efforts to increase awareness in underserved communities and awareness among individuals with disabilities (as defined in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s12102"},"text":"section 12102 of this title","children":[],"tail":") and Deaf individuals."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb529a783-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s280b–1b/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Collection and dissemination of information on sexual assault","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary shall, through the National Resource Center on Sexual Assault established under the National Center for Injury Prevention and Control at the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, provide resource information, policy, training, and technical assistance to Federal, State, local, and Indian Tribal agencies, as well as to State sexual assault coalitions and local sexual assault programs and to other professionals and interested parties on issues relating to sexual assault, including maintenance of a central resource library in order to collect, prepare, analyze, and disseminate information and statistics and analyses thereof relating to the incidence and prevention of sexual assault.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb529a784-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s280b–1b/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Meaningful involvement of State sexual assault coalitions, culturally specific organizations, and underserved communities","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In awarding funds to States under this section, the Secretary shall set forth procedures designed to ensure meaningful involvement of sexual assault coalitions, culturally specific organizations, and representatives from underserved communities of the State or territory in the application for, and implementation of, funding.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb529a785-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s280b–1b/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Authorization of appropriations","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb529a786-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s280b–1b/d/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" In general","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"There is authorized to be appropriated to carry out this section $100,000,000 for each of fiscal years 2023 through 2027.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb529a787-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s280b–1b/d/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" National sexual violence resource center allotment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Of the total amount made available under this subsection in each fiscal year, not less than $1,500,000 shall be available for allotment under subsection (b).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb529a788-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s280b–1b/d/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Baseline funding for States, the District of Columbia, and Puerto Rico","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A minimum allocation of $150,000 shall be awarded in each fiscal year for each of the States, the District of Columbia, and Puerto Rico. A minimum allocation of $35,000 shall be awarded in each fiscal year for each Territory. Any unused or remaining funds shall be allotted to each State, the District of Columbia, and Puerto Rico on the basis of population. Not less than 80 percent of the total amount made available under this subsection in each fiscal year shall be awarded in accordance with this paragraph.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb529a789-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s280b–1b/d/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" State, territorial, and Tribal sexual assault coalition allotment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb529a78a-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s280b–1b/d/4/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" In general","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Of the total amount appropriated under this subsection for a fiscal year, not less than 15 percent shall be allocated to State, territorial, and Tribal sexual assault coalitions for the purposes of coordinating and providing prevention activities, providing assistance to prevention programs, and collaborating and coordinating with applicable Federal, State, Tribal, and local entities engaged in sexual violence prevention, in accordance with this paragraph.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb529a78b-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s280b–1b/d/4/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Allocations","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"Of the total amount appropriated under this subsection and allocated to making awards to sexual assault coalitions, as described in subparagraph (A), for a fiscal year—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idb529a78c-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s280b–1b/d/4/B/i"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"i"},"text":"(i)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" not less than 10 percent shall be made available to Tribal sexual assault coalitions; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"idb529a78d-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s280b–1b/d/4/B/ii"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"ii"},"text":"(ii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" any remaining amounts shall be made available, in equal amounts, to each State coalition and each territorial coalition.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb529a78e-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s280b–1b/d/4/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Clarification","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Receipt of an award under this subsection by a sexual assault coalition shall not preclude the coalition from receiving additional grants or administering funds to carry out the purposes described in subsection (a).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb529a78f-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s280b–1b/e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"e"},"text":"(e)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Limitations","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb529a790-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s280b–1b/e/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Supplement not supplant","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amounts provided to States under this section shall be used to supplement and not supplant other Federal, State, and local public funds expended to provide services of the type described in subsection (a).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb529a791-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s280b–1b/e/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Studies","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A State may not use more than 2 percent of the amount received by the State under this section for each fiscal year for surveillance studies or prevalence studies.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb529a792-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s280b–1b/e/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Administration","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A State may not use more than 5 percent of the amount received by the State under this section for each fiscal year for administrative expenses.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb529a793-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s280b–1b/f"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"f"},"text":"(f)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Report","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Not later than 1 year after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2022-03-15"},"text":"March 15, 2022","children":[],"tail":", the Secretary, acting through the Director of the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, shall submit to the Committee on Appropriations, the Committee on Energy and Commerce, and the Committee on the Judiciary of the House of Representatives and the Committee on Appropriations, the Committee on Health, Education, Labor, and Pensions, and the Committee on the Judiciary of the Senate a report on the activities funded by grants awarded under this section and best practices relating to rape prevention and education."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idb529a794-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1944-07-01/ch373"},"text":"July 1, 1944, ch. 373","children":[],"tail":", title III, § 393A, formerly § 393B, as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/386/dB/tIV/s1401/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–386, div. B, title IV, § 1401(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-10-28"},"text":"Oct. 28, 2000","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/114/1512"},"text":"114 Stat. 1512","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/162/tIII/s302"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–162, title III, § 302","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2006-01-05"},"text":"Jan. 5, 2006","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/119/3004"},"text":"119 Stat. 3004","children":[],"tail":"; renumbered § 393C, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/202/s2/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–202, § 2(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2008-04-23"},"text":"Apr. 23, 2008","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/122/697"},"text":"122 Stat. 697","children":[],"tail":"; renumbered § 393A, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/206/s2/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–206, § 2(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2008-04-28"},"text":"Apr. 28, 2008","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/122/714"},"text":"122 Stat. 714","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/4/tIII/s301"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–4, title III, § 301","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2013-03-07"},"text":"Mar. 7, 2013","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/127/84"},"text":"127 Stat. 84","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/103/dW/tIII/s301"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–103, div. W, title III, § 301","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2022-03-15"},"text":"Mar. 15, 2022","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/136/863"},"text":"136 Stat. 863","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idb529a795-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idb529a796-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"idb529a797-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was formerly classified to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s280b–1c"},"text":"section 280b–1c of this title","children":[],"tail":". "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/206"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–206","children":[],"tail":", which directed the renumbering of “the section 393B ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s280b–1c"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 280b–1c","children":[],"tail":")” of act "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1944-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 1944","children":[],"tail":", “relating to the use of allotments for rape prevention education” as section 393A and the transfer of that section so as to appear after section 393 of that Act, was executed by renumbering section 393C of that Act as 393A and transferring the renumbered provisions to this section, to reflect the probable intent of Congress and the renumbering of section 393B as 393C by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/202/s2/1"},"text":"section 2(1) of Pub. L. 110–202","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"priorProvisions","id":"idb529a798-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Prior Provisions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A prior section 393A of act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1944-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 1944","children":[],"tail":", was renumbered section 393B and is classified to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s280b–1c"},"text":"section 280b–1c of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idb529a799-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2022—Subsec. (a)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/103/s301/1/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–103, § 301(1)(A)","children":[],"tail":", inserted before semicolon at end “or utilization of other communication technologies for purposes related to such a hotline”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/103/s301/1/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–103, § 301(1)(B)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “professionals, including school-based professionals, to identify and refer students who may have experienced or are at risk of experiencing sexual violence” for “professionals”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(7). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/103/s301/1/C"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–103, § 301(1)(C)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “sexual violence, sexual assault, and sexual harassment” for “sexual assault” and inserted “and Deaf individuals” before period at end."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/103/s301/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–103, § 301(2)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “Indian Tribal” for “Indian tribal”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/103/s301/4"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–103, § 301(4)","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (c). Former subsec. (c) redesignated (d)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/103/s301/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–103, § 301(3)","children":[],"tail":", redesignated subsec. (c) as (d). Former subsec. (d) redesignated (e)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/103/s301/5/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–103, § 301(5)(A)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “$100,000,000 for each of fiscal years 2023 through 2027” for “$50,000,000 for each of fiscal years 2014 through 2018”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d)(3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/103/s301/5/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–103, § 301(5)(B)","children":[],"tail":", inserted at end “Not less than 80 percent of the total amount made available under this subsection in each fiscal year shall be awarded in accordance with this paragraph.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d)(4). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/103/s301/5/C"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–103, § 301(5)(C)","children":[],"tail":", added par. (4)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (e). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/103/s301/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–103, § 301(3)","children":[],"tail":", redesignated subsec. (d) as (e)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (f). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/103/s301/6"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–103, § 301(6)","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (f)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2013—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/4/s301/1/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–4, § 301(1)(A)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “, territorial or tribal” after “crisis centers, State” in introductory provisions."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(6). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/4/s301/1/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–4, § 301(1)(B)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “and alcohol” after “about drugs”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/4/s301/2/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–4, § 301(2)(A)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “$50,000,000 for each of fiscal years 2014 through 2018” for “$80,000,000 for each of fiscal years 2007 through 2011”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"hr